1.2.1 Self-consistent model

Mantič-Lugo et al. [7] developed the self-consistent model to describe the amplitude saturation process without time integration. This model is a coupled system consisting of the mean ﬂow governing equation and linearized Navier-Stokes equations. Mantič-Lugo et al. [7] assumed that for supercritical ﬂows satisfying the RZIF property, the leading mode suﬃces for the mean ﬂow distortion. Therefore, the self-consistent model is written as

