3.2.7 Hilbert transform

We use the Hilbert transform to obtain spatial characteristics of the ﬂow. The Hilbert transform is a useful means of extracting the local amplitude and phase from a signal. A complex analytic signal fa(x) is constructed from real data f (x). In contrast to a real signal that has negative and positive frequencies, fa is complex and has only positive frequencies. This signal is obtained by

fa(x) = f (x) + iH(f (x))

(3.15)

