Equations (5.19) and (5.20) are the cornerstone of the linearization about the mean ﬁelds [1, 13, 14, 16, 20] and of the self-consistent model developed in [9] and described in section 5.4.
The RZIF procedure calls for neglecting the nonlinear self-interactions from equations (5.20). We then obtain the governing equations of the linear stability analysis about the mean

∂tu = LU (u )

(5.22)

Since (5.22) is linear in u and homogeneous in t, its solutions are again of the form u (x, z, t) = e(σ+iω)tu˜(x, z), leading again to the eigenproblem

